Durban - Police are investigating a case of murder after a man was found dead floating in the Duzi River in Alexander Pietermaritzburg. ER 24 spokesperson, Russel Meiring, said efforts to resuscitate the man believed to be his 30s, were unsuccessful. Meiring said they were alerted to the incident on Wednesday afternoon. "ER24 paramedics, along with the SAPS Search and Rescue, arrived on the scene to find the body of a man lying in the river. " Meiring said after the man was successfully retrieved and assessed they found he sustained a gunshot wound to his leg. "He also sustained numerous wounds to his back," added Meiring. He said paramedics immediately initiated CPR and advanced life support interventions. "Unfortunately, after 45 minutes, no vital signs returned and the man was declared dead." KZN police spokesperson, Captain Nqobile Gwala, said a case of murder had been opened.  No arrests had been made. Daily News